# Agent Knowledge Base

Before executing tasks in this project, read **`docs/AGENTS_KNOWLEDGE.md`** (project root) for:

- Repository layout and critical file paths
- Entry points (run_predictions.py, app.py, setup_wizard, etc.) and how to run
- Configuration: .env, feature_flags.yaml, profiles.yaml, src/config.py
- Data flow (sync → rolling → composite → value → card)
- Conventions and known tech debt (so you don’t “fix” intentional behavior)
- User expectations (PR for changes, no breakage, realistic feedback)
- Project charter (stopping rules, bootstrap phases, go-live gates)
- Where to change what (quick reference table)

That document is the single source of truth for AI agents. Prefer updating `docs/AGENTS_KNOWLEDGE.md` when you add entry points, config, or conventions so future agents stay in sync.
